# Code owners for smart-router.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the matching owner on every PR that
# touches a path below, and (when "Require review from Code Owners" is on
# in branch protection) that review is required to satisfy the PR gate in
# .github/workflows/pr-gate-on-approval.yml.
#
# Order matters: the LAST matching pattern wins. The catch-all comes first
# so more specific rules below can override it.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @Magma-Devs/r-d

# Release & supply-chain surface — the security-sensitive plumbing called
# out in SECURITY.md (release pipeline is explicitly in scope). Changes
# here move the :latest pointer, sign artifacts, and build the published
# image, so they get the same owner as the rest but are pinned out
# explicitly to make the blast radius obvious in review.
/.goreleaser.yaml       @Magma-Devs/r-d
/.github/workflows/     @Magma-Devs/r-d
/docker/                @Magma-Devs/r-d

# Licensing & legal text — keep dual-license wording under review so a
# stray edit can't quietly change the commercial terms.
/LICENSE.md             @Magma-Devs/r-d
/LICENSING.md           @Magma-Devs/r-d
